[93.792927, "i", "cat > FIXES_APPLIED.txt << 'EOF'\nEXPORT SCRIPT FIXES - Applied on $(date)\n================================================\n\nProblem: export_users.sh was producing garbled CSV output after migration\nto multi-file format. Symptoms included:\n- UIDs appearing in email column\n- GIDs showing instead of group names\n- Incorrect data alignment\n\nRoot Causes Identified:\n\n1. WRONG DELIMITER FOR emails.dat\n   - File uses TAB delimiter but script used space delimiter\n   - Caused entire \"uid<TAB>email\" to be treated as single field\n   - Fix: Changed cut -d' ' to awk -F$'\\t' for proper tab handling\n\n2. SORTING MISMATCH (noted but already handled via awk lookup)\n   - Users sorted alphabetically, emails sorted numerically\n   - Fixed by using awk lookup instead of paste/join\n\n3. WRONG FIELD SEPARATOR FOR groups.dat\n   - File uses colon delimiter (gid:name:description)\n   - Script used awk default (space/tab) so whole line became $1\n   - Fix: Added -F':' to all awk commands processing groups.dat\n\nResults:\n- All 800 users exporte"]
[93.793079, "i", "d successfully\n- Clean CSV with proper field separation\n- Group names resolved correctly (primary and supplementary)\n- Emails clean without UID prefixes\n\nBackup of original script: export_users.sh.backup\nEOF\n"]
[93.793141, "o", "cat > FIXES_APPLIED.txt << 'EOF'\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
